1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,002
<i>Liam!</i>

2
00:00:03,086 --> 00:00:03,962
<i>Liam!</i>

3
00:00:04,921 --> 00:00:08,258
[ICE] <i>Can you imagine?</i>
<i>Our issues were so petty.</i>

4
00:00:08,341 --> 00:00:10,677
<i>If only I could turn back time.</i>

5
00:00:11,469 --> 00:00:15,473
<i>I understand where you're coming from.</i>
<i>That's what I'm thinking about too.</i>

6
00:00:15,557 --> 00:00:16,933
<i>If only</i>

7
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:19,686
<i>I could turn back time.</i>

8
00:00:19,769 --> 00:00:23,356
[NURSE] <i>St. John's already coordinating</i>
<i>with other hospitals and blood banks.</i>

9
00:00:23,440 --> 00:00:24,357
[ICE] <i>It's Liam.</i>

10
00:00:24,441 --> 00:00:26,276
<i>Are you okay now? How are you?</i>

11
00:00:26,359 --> 00:00:27,360
<i>I'm okay now.</i>

12
00:00:27,444 --> 00:00:29,279
<i>But Papa isn't.</i>
<i>He was shot.</i>

13
00:00:29,362 --> 00:00:31,781
<i>He lost a lot of blood.</i>
<i>He needs a blood transfusion.</i>

14
00:00:31,865 --> 00:00:33,450
<i>But there's a blood shortage.</i>

15
00:00:33,533 --> 00:00:37,454
<i>Blood supplies compatible with B negative</i>
<i>have run out everywhere in Alicante.</i>

16
00:00:37,537 --> 00:00:39,914
[CLEARS THROAT]
<i>My blood type's B negative.</i>

17
00:00:44,127 --> 00:00:45,670
<i>It's going to be okay, Ma.</i>

18
00:00:45,754 --> 00:00:49,632
<i>We've done everything we can,</i>
<i>Mrs. Bonifacio.</i>

19
00:00:49,716 --> 00:00:50,967
<i>Unfortunately,</i>

20
00:00:51,050 --> 00:00:54,012
<i>he's showing no signs of improvement.</i>

21
00:00:54,095 --> 00:00:57,932
<i>The next 24 hours</i>
<i>will be much more critical.</i>

22
00:00:58,016 --> 00:01:00,351
[MAGNUS] <i>My sins are catching up with me.</i>

23
00:01:00,435 --> 00:01:01,603
<i>It doesn't matter now.</i>

24
00:01:01,686 --> 00:01:03,146
<i>Emil's dead.</i>

25
00:01:03,229 --> 00:01:07,067
<i>We won't stop until we get our revenge.</i>

26
00:01:09,652 --> 00:01:11,196
[LUCAS CHUCKLES EXCITEDLY]

27
00:01:11,279 --> 00:01:14,449
- [INSECTS CHIRRING]
- [BREATHING DEEPLY]

28
00:01:18,078 --> 00:01:20,205
[LEAVES RUSTLING]

29
00:01:20,288 --> 00:01:23,208
[LUCAS GRUNTING SOFTLY]

30
00:01:26,461 --> 00:01:29,047
[LUCAS] Dado, lend me a hand.

31
00:01:29,130 --> 00:01:30,048
Now pull.

32
00:01:30,131 --> 00:01:32,509
- [LUCAS, DADO GRUNTING]
- [GATES CREAKING]

33
00:01:32,592 --> 00:01:34,010
[LUCAS HUFFS]

34
00:01:36,095 --> 00:01:39,724
[LUCAS PANTING]

35
00:01:39,808 --> 00:01:40,767
[LEVER CLICKS]

36
00:01:40,850 --> 00:01:44,062
- [LIGHT BULBS CRACKLE]
- [AIR WHOOSHING]

37
00:01:44,145 --> 00:01:47,774
[ALL CHUCKLING MANIACALLY]

38
00:01:48,441 --> 00:01:50,777
Dado, help me with this.

39
00:01:52,070 --> 00:01:53,196
One, two…

40
00:01:53,279 --> 00:01:59,327
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

41
00:02:00,787 --> 00:02:01,788
Why isn't it here?!

42
00:02:02,956 --> 00:02:04,249
Huh?

43
00:02:05,542 --> 00:02:07,544
- Someone stole it.
- [DADO] Wow!

44
00:02:08,169 --> 00:02:09,420
[DADO] Isn't that obvious?

45
00:02:09,504 --> 00:02:11,256
Of course someone stole it!

46
00:02:12,048 --> 00:02:13,758
[EMIL] That's enough!

47
00:02:14,634 --> 00:02:19,264
Who else knew you'd stashed
the money and jewelry here?

48
00:02:20,181 --> 00:02:22,767
The goons knew,
but they've already been taken out!

49
00:02:22,851 --> 00:02:26,062
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

50
00:02:26,146 --> 00:02:27,981
<i>Where are you taking those?</i>

51
00:02:28,064 --> 00:02:30,191
<i>Boss Emil's a cautious man.</i>

52
00:02:30,275 --> 00:02:33,695
<i>If things go south,</i>
<i>we need to keep the loot safe.</i>

53
00:02:37,782 --> 00:02:39,367
Jacinto!

54
00:02:40,660 --> 00:02:41,703
What?

55
00:02:41,786 --> 00:02:43,329
Jacinto knew!

56
00:02:43,413 --> 00:02:44,914
He stole all of it!

57
00:02:44,998 --> 00:02:46,291
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

58
00:02:46,374 --> 00:02:48,251
[GRUNTS, GROANS]

59
00:02:49,168 --> 00:02:50,962
Any news on Jacinto?

60
00:02:51,671 --> 00:02:53,089
Well?

61
00:02:54,090 --> 00:02:56,676
[LUCAS BREATHING HEAVILY]

62
00:03:00,388 --> 00:03:02,307
This is ridiculous!

63
00:03:03,474 --> 00:03:05,393
[EXCLAIMS IN ANGER]

64
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:10,398
[MONITOR BEEPS]

65
00:03:12,650 --> 00:03:17,989
- [BEEPING STEADILY]
- [STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

66
00:03:20,867 --> 00:03:27,332
[MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

67
00:03:36,382 --> 00:03:43,264
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

68
00:04:12,168 --> 00:04:13,419
[REPORTER ON TV] <i>Currently,</i>

69
00:04:13,503 --> 00:04:16,214
<i>the possible involvement</i>
<i>of Captain Jericho Jacinto</i>

70
00:04:16,297 --> 00:04:20,718
<i>in the hostage incident at La Playa Roja</i>
<i>is still under investigation.</i>

71
00:04:20,802 --> 00:04:22,929
<i>In connection with this,</i>
<i>there is still no news</i>

72
00:04:23,012 --> 00:04:26,724
<i>regarding his condition at</i>
<i>St. John's Hospital in Alicante.</i>

73
00:04:26,808 --> 00:04:27,642
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

74
00:04:27,725 --> 00:04:29,644
[LIAM] He'll pay for all he did.

75
00:04:29,727 --> 00:04:32,397
[RINGING CONTINUES]

76
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:34,065
Son.

77
00:04:34,148 --> 00:04:36,317
He almost killed you.

78
00:04:36,401 --> 00:04:38,987
I hope he doesn't survive.

79
00:04:39,570 --> 00:04:41,698
Thank you for saving my life, Ma.

80
00:04:42,490 --> 00:04:44,701
But Captain Jericho can't die just yet.

81
00:04:44,784 --> 00:04:46,661
He needs to wake up

82
00:04:46,744 --> 00:04:49,747
and answer to the families
of the victims at the resort.

83
00:04:50,456 --> 00:04:53,084
He'll be held accountable
for all those innocent lives.

84
00:04:53,167 --> 00:04:56,838
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

85
00:04:56,921 --> 00:04:57,964
Olsen.

86
00:04:59,173 --> 00:05:00,341
How's your grandpa?

87
00:05:02,969 --> 00:05:04,429
Still no good news.

88
00:05:05,555 --> 00:05:08,474
Don't lose hope, Olsen.

89
00:05:11,102 --> 00:05:12,103
Yeah.

90
00:05:12,895 --> 00:05:13,980
What, uh…

91
00:05:14,647 --> 00:05:16,774
What about Sir Magnus? Is he okay?

92
00:05:16,858 --> 00:05:22,196
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

93
00:05:25,950 --> 00:05:27,827
Olsen, I owe you.

94
00:05:27,910 --> 00:05:29,454
Thank you, Olsen.

95
00:05:29,537 --> 00:05:30,747
It's nothing, sir.

96
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:35,710
I know you would've done

97
00:05:35,793 --> 00:05:38,713
the same thing
if the situation were reversed.

98
00:05:40,798 --> 00:05:44,302
You're lucky Olsen shares
your blood type, Pa.

99
00:05:44,385 --> 00:05:47,513
I'm your own child, and we don't share it.

100
00:05:47,597 --> 00:05:49,640
Liam…
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

101
00:05:49,724 --> 00:05:52,393
Not all kids and parents
share the same blood type.

102
00:05:52,477 --> 00:05:53,978
[MUSIC BECOMES INTRIGUING]

103
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:57,398
With me and Sir Magnus?
It's just a coincidence.

104
00:05:58,566 --> 00:05:59,942
But then again,

105
00:06:01,069 --> 00:06:02,737
even when I was little,

106
00:06:03,446 --> 00:06:04,989
I already saw you as a father figure.

107
00:06:05,073 --> 00:06:10,536
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

108
00:06:13,539 --> 00:06:16,667
[TENSE, PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

109
00:06:16,751 --> 00:06:17,919
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

110
00:06:18,586 --> 00:06:21,422
[TENSE, PENSIVE MUSIC KEEPS PLAYING]

111
00:06:29,764 --> 00:06:31,140
[WENDY] <i>Uh…</i>

112
00:06:33,935 --> 00:06:34,894
[GRETA] <i>You have a son?</i>

113
00:06:34,977 --> 00:06:38,439
[WENDY]<i> I'm sorry I didn't say goodbye.</i>

114
00:06:38,523 --> 00:06:40,274
<i>I knew you'd be angry.</i>

115
00:06:40,358 --> 00:06:42,693
<i>I left with Gardo,</i>

116
00:06:42,777 --> 00:06:47,365
<i>the bodyguard</i>
<i>of one of our guests at the resort.</i>

117
00:06:47,448 --> 00:06:49,700
<i>When I was pregnant with Olsen,</i>

118
00:06:49,784 --> 00:06:52,286
<i>he had a heart attack.</i>

119
00:06:52,370 --> 00:06:55,623
<i>That's why we never got married.</i>

120
00:06:55,706 --> 00:07:00,795
<i>My father's small salary as</i>
<i>a security guard isn't enough.</i>

121
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:06,008
<i>I don't even know where to find money</i>
<i>for Olsen's operation.</i>

122
00:07:06,092 --> 00:07:10,430
[TENSE, PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

123
00:07:10,513 --> 00:07:11,973
- [DOOR OPENS]
- [RADIO CRACKLES]

124
00:07:12,056 --> 00:07:13,474
[POLICE OFFICER] Negative.

125
00:07:13,558 --> 00:07:16,436
Visitors are still not allowed
for Captain Jacinto.

126
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:19,564
Yes, he's in stable condition in Room 202.

127
00:07:20,982 --> 00:07:22,066
[RADIO CRACKLES]

128
00:07:25,069 --> 00:07:29,240
[TENSE, PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

129
00:07:29,323 --> 00:07:31,868
[MONITOR BEEPING]

130
00:07:34,745 --> 00:07:37,582
I'm glad you're back to being
friends again with Olsen.

131
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:41,544
You know, I miss the days
when it felt as though

132
00:07:41,627 --> 00:07:43,254
I had two sons.

133
00:07:43,337 --> 00:07:49,135
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

134
00:07:49,218 --> 00:07:50,344
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

135
00:07:51,512 --> 00:07:52,763
Come in.

136
00:07:58,978 --> 00:08:00,521
[DOOR CREAKING]

137
00:08:04,734 --> 00:08:06,694
How are you feeling now, Magnus?

138
00:08:07,445 --> 00:08:10,698
Thanks to your son,
I feel so much better now.

139
00:08:10,781 --> 00:08:12,492
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

140
00:08:12,575 --> 00:08:15,036
Where's Greta?

141
00:08:15,119 --> 00:08:17,079
She was here not long ago.

142
00:08:17,163 --> 00:08:18,456
Why?

143
00:08:19,290 --> 00:08:22,084
I just wanted to apologize to her.

144
00:08:22,168 --> 00:08:25,004
Wendy, I feel that's not necessary.

145
00:08:27,423 --> 00:08:30,468
Uh, what happened back at La Playa Roja,

146
00:08:30,551 --> 00:08:33,679
all those terrible memories we had there…

147
00:08:35,765 --> 00:08:38,476
let's just put them behind us.

148
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:41,854
- [SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]
- I was hoping to talk to her.

149
00:08:44,857 --> 00:08:46,359
I'll go look for her.

150
00:08:47,193 --> 00:08:48,444
[MAGNUS] All right.

151
00:08:53,616 --> 00:08:56,702
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

152
00:08:59,413 --> 00:09:01,832
[WAVES LAPPING]

153
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:04,210
[LUCAS CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

154
00:09:04,293 --> 00:09:06,003
- Brother!
- Lucas!

155
00:09:06,087 --> 00:09:06,921
Homer!

156
00:09:07,004 --> 00:09:09,757
- [GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]
- [BOTH LAUGH]

157
00:09:11,259 --> 00:09:12,426
Homer.

158
00:09:13,928 --> 00:09:16,305
Lucas, thank you.

159
00:09:16,389 --> 00:09:17,640
[CHUCKLES, BREATHES DEEPLY]

160
00:09:17,723 --> 00:09:19,267
Good thing you made that call.

161
00:09:19,350 --> 00:09:21,477
I thought we'd never see each other again.

162
00:09:22,311 --> 00:09:24,939
[LUCAS, HOMER LAUGHING]

163
00:09:25,982 --> 00:09:27,066
Dado, how's it going?

164
00:09:27,149 --> 00:09:28,442
- [HOMER] Boss Emil.
- Homer.

165
00:09:28,526 --> 00:09:30,987
These are the guys Lucas and I
used to work with.

166
00:09:31,070 --> 00:09:34,073
Fredo, Roman, and Conrad.

167
00:09:34,156 --> 00:09:37,368
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

168
00:09:37,451 --> 00:09:39,328
Everyone, meet Boss Emil, our new boss.

169
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:46,919
So, where's our cargo?

170
00:09:47,795 --> 00:09:51,257
That's the problem, Homer. It's missing.
Someone stole everything.

171
00:09:51,924 --> 00:09:52,842
Who?

172
00:09:52,925 --> 00:09:59,765
I'm sure Jacinto knows
where our millions of pesos have gone.

173
00:10:00,516 --> 00:10:01,684
Jacinto?

174
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:04,103
The cop who recruited you?

175
00:10:04,186 --> 00:10:05,646
[EMIL] Yes, Homer.

176
00:10:06,647 --> 00:10:09,275
He's the police officer I worked with.

177
00:10:09,358 --> 00:10:12,903
He's the one
who recruited and betrayed us.

178
00:10:12,987 --> 00:10:14,905
Where is he now?

179
00:10:14,989 --> 00:10:18,200
He's in a hospital in Alicante.

180
00:10:18,284 --> 00:10:20,453
And that's where we're going.

181
00:10:20,536 --> 00:10:26,959
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

182
00:10:27,043 --> 00:10:32,715
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

183
00:10:39,305 --> 00:10:45,519
- [EKG BEEPING STEADILY]
- [SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

184
00:10:49,607 --> 00:10:50,608
<i>Olsen.</i>

185
00:10:51,567 --> 00:10:53,569
<i>We're not taking sides.</i>

186
00:10:54,904 --> 00:10:59,241
<i>All I'm saying, grandson,</i>
<i>is that you've got this all wrong.</i>

187
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:01,118
<i>Keep an open mind!</i>

188
00:11:01,952 --> 00:11:03,537
<i>Grandpa, I'm your grandson.</i>

189
00:11:03,621 --> 00:11:06,165
<i>- I know. But try to understand!</i>
- [WENDY SOBS]

190
00:11:06,248 --> 00:11:08,834
<i>Why does it feel like</i>
<i>Liam is more important to you?</i>

191
00:11:10,169 --> 00:11:12,129
- [BEN] <i>Wait--</i>
- [WENDY] <i>Pa, let it be.</i>

192
00:11:12,213 --> 00:11:14,382
[WENDY] <i>Pa, no.</i>
<i>Let's give him some time.</i>

193
00:11:15,674 --> 00:11:17,927
Grandpa?
[SNIFFLES]

194
00:11:18,010 --> 00:11:20,763
[CRIES, SNIFFLES]

195
00:11:20,846 --> 00:11:22,765
I know when…
[SNIFFLES]

196
00:11:22,848 --> 00:11:24,809
…we last talked…
[CRIES SHAKILY]

197
00:11:24,892 --> 00:11:26,977
[EKG BEEPING STEADILY]

198
00:11:27,061 --> 00:11:29,188
…we weren't on good terms.

199
00:11:29,271 --> 00:11:31,524
I was so stubborn.

200
00:11:32,149 --> 00:11:33,984
But I hope…

201
00:11:35,069 --> 00:11:37,488
[CRIES SHAKILY, SNIFFLES]

202
00:11:37,571 --> 00:11:39,740
…you can hear me.

203
00:11:42,326 --> 00:11:44,245
I hope you can feel me right now.

204
00:11:44,328 --> 00:11:46,956
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

205
00:11:47,039 --> 00:11:48,958
I'm so sorry, Grandpa.
[SOBS SHAKILY]

206
00:11:52,253 --> 00:11:53,462
I'm sorry.

207
00:11:55,089 --> 00:11:56,966
I understand you.

208
00:11:57,967 --> 00:11:59,677
[CRIES] I understand you now.

209
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:05,349
I know I shouldn't… [SOBS]
I shouldn't have gotten angry so quickly.

210
00:12:05,433 --> 00:12:07,977
I shouldn't have blamed anyone.
[SOBS SHAKILY]

211
00:12:09,395 --> 00:12:11,564
I understand everything you said.

212
00:12:13,065 --> 00:12:14,442
I-I don't know why…

213
00:12:16,444 --> 00:12:20,448
I don't know why things
had to get this tough. [SOBS]

214
00:12:20,531 --> 00:12:22,575
[EKG CONTINUES BEEPING]

215
00:12:23,159 --> 00:12:25,453
[SOBS] I'm so sorry, Grandpa.

216
00:12:25,536 --> 00:12:27,371
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

217
00:12:27,455 --> 00:12:28,998
[SOBS SHAKILY, SNIFFLES]

218
00:12:29,081 --> 00:12:30,708
But, Grandpa…
[SOBS]

219
00:12:32,168 --> 00:12:33,627
Liam and I are on good terms now.

220
00:12:33,711 --> 00:12:35,588
That's what you wanted, right?

221
00:12:36,297 --> 00:12:38,716
I hope you know that. [SOBS]

222
00:12:39,383 --> 00:12:41,427
[SOBS] But, Grandpa…

223
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:42,678
[BREATH QUIVERS]

224
00:12:42,761 --> 00:12:46,348
- [EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]
- [SOBS SHAKILY]

225
00:12:46,432 --> 00:12:49,101
There's just one thing I want to tell you.

226
00:12:50,019 --> 00:12:50,978
Thank you, Grandpa.

227
00:12:51,061 --> 00:12:53,022
[SOBBING SHAKILY]

228
00:12:53,105 --> 00:12:56,275
You shouldn't be the one lying there.
It should've been me.

229
00:12:56,358 --> 00:12:58,027
[SOBBING SHAKILY]

230
00:12:58,110 --> 00:13:00,988
I should be the one lying there, Grandpa.

231
00:13:01,071 --> 00:13:03,908
[SOBS] You saved me.

232
00:13:04,617 --> 00:13:06,744
Thank you, Grandpa.
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

233
00:13:07,536 --> 00:13:09,830
You always put your grandson first.

234
00:13:10,456 --> 00:13:11,332
[SOBS]

235
00:13:11,415 --> 00:13:13,626
I'm so sorry, Grandpa.

236
00:13:13,709 --> 00:13:15,669
[EKG BEEPING STEADILY]

237
00:13:15,753 --> 00:13:19,131
[EKG BEEPING RAPIDLY, FLATLINES]

238
00:13:19,215 --> 00:13:20,382
[OLSEN] What's…?

239
00:13:20,466 --> 00:13:21,675
[ALARM GOING OFF]

240
00:13:21,759 --> 00:13:23,552
[NURSE] Code blue! Code blue!

241
00:13:23,636 --> 00:13:25,221
N-Nurse?

242
00:13:25,304 --> 00:13:27,473
Nurse! What's happening?!

243
00:13:27,556 --> 00:13:29,725
- Nurse!
- Sir, please step outside.

244
00:13:29,808 --> 00:13:30,809
Huh? Why?

245
00:13:30,893 --> 00:13:32,811
- Sir, please.
- Grandpa! [SOBS SHAKILY]

246
00:13:32,895 --> 00:13:34,688
- Sir.
- Grandpa!

247
00:13:34,772 --> 00:13:37,274
Just hold on, Grandpa! I'm here for you!

248
00:13:37,358 --> 00:13:38,817
Grandpa! [SNIFFLES]

249
00:13:38,901 --> 00:13:40,277
Grandpa! [BREATHES HEAVILY]

250
00:13:40,361 --> 00:13:42,363
Nurse, this can't--

251
00:13:42,446 --> 00:13:44,490
T-This can't happen! [SOBS]

252
00:13:44,573 --> 00:13:51,413
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

253
00:13:55,584 --> 00:13:57,336
- [KNOCKING]
- [OLSEN] Grandpa!

254
00:13:57,419 --> 00:13:59,088
[DOCTOR] Time of death: 11:30 p.m.

255
00:13:59,171 --> 00:14:01,382
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

256
00:14:01,465 --> 00:14:02,758
[OLSEN] Doc, wait.

257
00:14:02,841 --> 00:14:03,884
Doc!

258
00:14:03,968 --> 00:14:05,636
Doc, what happened?

259
00:14:05,719 --> 00:14:08,138
[SIGHS] I'm sorry,
but we can't do anything--

260
00:14:08,222 --> 00:14:10,975
[OLSEN] What do you mean?! No, don't stop!

261
00:14:13,435 --> 00:14:15,479
[CRYING] Grandpa.

262
00:14:15,563 --> 00:14:20,025
<i>Grandpa! Grandpa! Grandpa--</i>
[SOBBING]

263
00:14:20,109 --> 00:14:21,902
<i>Grandpa!</i>

264
00:14:21,986 --> 00:14:24,196
[SORROWFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

265
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,240
[SOBS] Grandpa!

266
00:14:26,323 --> 00:14:28,033
Why?!

267
00:14:28,117 --> 00:14:29,827
[SOBBING]

268
00:14:31,161 --> 00:14:32,454
Grandpa!

269
00:14:33,414 --> 00:14:38,627
- [SOBBING CONTINUES]
- [SORROWFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

270
00:14:38,711 --> 00:14:39,962
Grandpa!

271
00:14:40,963 --> 00:14:47,720
- [SOBBING CONTINUES]
- [SORROWFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

272
00:14:47,803 --> 00:14:49,555
Why?! [SOBS]

273
00:14:49,638 --> 00:14:54,935
- [SORROWFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [SOBBING]

274
00:14:55,019 --> 00:14:56,562
<i>Why, Grandpa?!</i>

275
00:14:57,688 --> 00:14:59,523
<i>Grandpa, why?!</i>

276
00:14:59,607 --> 00:15:02,860
[SORROWFUL MUSIC SWELLS
THEN FADES]

277
00:15:07,698 --> 00:15:10,701
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

278
00:15:10,784 --> 00:15:15,247
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

279
00:15:15,331 --> 00:15:22,338
- [SINISTER MUSIC PLAYING]
- [RINGING CONTINUES, STOPS]

280
00:15:26,050 --> 00:15:28,719
- Um…
- [POLICE OFFICER CLEARS THROAT]

281
00:15:28,802 --> 00:15:30,346
Ma'am Greta.

282
00:15:30,429 --> 00:15:31,555
Uh…

283
00:15:31,639 --> 00:15:34,183
How is Captain Jacinto?

284
00:15:34,266 --> 00:15:36,101
He still hasn't woken up.

285
00:15:36,852 --> 00:15:38,771
May I see him?

286
00:15:38,854 --> 00:15:40,397
It won't take long.

287
00:15:40,481 --> 00:15:43,359
He's a trusted friend.

288
00:15:43,943 --> 00:15:46,236
All right, ma'am. Please come in.

289
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:47,947
[GRETA SIGHS]

290
00:15:48,030 --> 00:15:51,200
- [EKG BEEPS]
- [DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

291
00:15:51,283 --> 00:15:58,290
- [FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]
- [EKG BEEPING STEADILY]

292
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:05,589
- [INHALES SHARPLY]
- [DOOR CLICKS SHUT]

293
00:16:05,673 --> 00:16:12,513
- [FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [EKG CONTINUES BEEPING]

294
00:16:21,355 --> 00:16:26,777
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]
- [EKG CONTINUES BEEPING]

295
00:16:30,948 --> 00:16:33,534
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

296
00:16:33,617 --> 00:16:37,746
[MUFFLED SCREAMING]

297
00:16:40,416 --> 00:16:41,667
[JACINTO FALLS SILENT]

298
00:16:41,750 --> 00:16:47,172
- [DARK MUSIC SWELLS]
- [EKG FLATLINES]

299
00:16:47,256 --> 00:16:51,010
- [TELEPHONE RINGING]
- [EKG BEEPING STEADILY]

300
00:16:51,093 --> 00:16:53,095
I want to pray…

301
00:16:55,097 --> 00:16:57,057
that you finally die.

302
00:16:57,141 --> 00:16:58,726
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

303
00:16:58,809 --> 00:17:01,895
But I don't know

304
00:17:01,979 --> 00:17:04,523
if God will listen to me.

305
00:17:07,359 --> 00:17:10,237
But there's one thing
I can assure you of, Jericho.

306
00:17:12,239 --> 00:17:14,658
Only your reputation will be ruined.

307
00:17:16,702 --> 00:17:19,830
I won't let you drag me down.

308
00:17:19,913 --> 00:17:22,541
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

309
00:17:22,624 --> 00:17:26,003
No one will believe you
if you try to go up against me.

310
00:17:28,172 --> 00:17:29,631
You can't.

311
00:17:30,966 --> 00:17:32,968
No one

312
00:17:34,178 --> 00:17:38,140
will ruin my reputation or my family's.

313
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:41,060
No one.

314
00:17:41,143 --> 00:17:43,854
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

315
00:17:43,937 --> 00:17:46,023
[DOOR CLICKS OPEN, CREAKING]

316
00:17:46,106 --> 00:17:48,817
Ma'am, I'm sorry,
but you need to leave now.

317
00:17:48,901 --> 00:17:50,569
- No visitors are allowed.
- [SNIFFLES]

318
00:17:50,652 --> 00:17:52,654
I only made an exception for you.

319
00:17:54,406 --> 00:17:55,741
I will pray for him.

320
00:17:55,824 --> 00:18:02,414
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

321
00:18:07,377 --> 00:18:13,842
[WAVES LAPPING, SPLASHING]

322
00:18:21,892 --> 00:18:26,980
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

323
00:18:27,064 --> 00:18:33,904
[MUSIC BECOMES TENSE]

324
00:18:33,987 --> 00:18:40,160
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

325
00:18:41,912 --> 00:18:45,624
I hope Greta and I can patch things up.

326
00:18:45,707 --> 00:18:48,836
Greta and I promised each other that

327
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:52,381
we'd leave the past behind.

328
00:18:52,965 --> 00:18:55,175
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

329
00:18:56,176 --> 00:18:58,887
That's what I want too, Magnus.

330
00:19:00,848 --> 00:19:02,891
And I hope

331
00:19:03,767 --> 00:19:06,395
my best friend and I…

332
00:19:08,897 --> 00:19:11,400
can rebuild our relationship.
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

333
00:19:13,026 --> 00:19:16,613
Honestly, Wendy,
I don't think it'll be that easy.

334
00:19:16,697 --> 00:19:18,157
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

335
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:21,451
But it's still possible.

336
00:19:23,579 --> 00:19:24,663
I hope so.

337
00:19:25,372 --> 00:19:27,749
[TENSE STINGER]

338
00:19:27,833 --> 00:19:29,918
<i>Why are you so kind to me?</i>

339
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:34,006
<i>Didn't we make a promise</i>
<i>back in high school?</i>

340
00:19:34,089 --> 00:19:35,966
<i>- Always together!</i>
<i>- Always together!</i>

341
00:19:36,049 --> 00:19:38,302
<i>- Best friends for life!</i>
<i>- Best friends for life!</i>

342
00:19:38,385 --> 00:19:39,636
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

343
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:41,680
Greta knows…

344
00:19:43,932 --> 00:19:46,101
about what happened
between us in the past.

345
00:19:46,185 --> 00:19:47,853
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

346
00:19:47,936 --> 00:19:50,772
She still let me work at the resort,
didn't she?

347
00:19:50,856 --> 00:19:54,818
- [SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [WENDY SIGHS DEEPLY]

348
00:19:54,902 --> 00:19:56,653
[DOOR OPENS]

349
00:19:56,737 --> 00:19:58,989
[CRIES SHAKILY]

350
00:19:59,072 --> 00:20:00,657
Ma.
[SOBBING SHAKILY]

351
00:20:04,119 --> 00:20:05,579
Grandpa…

352
00:20:05,662 --> 00:20:07,206
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

353
00:20:10,417 --> 00:20:12,294
[VOICE BREAKS] Grandpa's gone.

354
00:20:12,878 --> 00:20:14,463
[SOBS] He's gone.

355
00:20:14,546 --> 00:20:17,424
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

356
00:20:18,967 --> 00:20:23,513
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
- [BOTH SOBBING]

357
00:20:23,597 --> 00:20:30,312
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

358
00:20:37,527 --> 00:20:39,821
I'm sorry, Wendy, Olsen.

359
00:20:39,905 --> 00:20:41,740
We're one family here.

360
00:20:42,282 --> 00:20:48,830
- [SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [SOBBING]

361
00:20:48,914 --> 00:20:54,503
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

362
00:21:02,844 --> 00:21:05,681
<i>We need to be careful</i>
<i>in attacking Jacinto.</i>

363
00:21:05,764 --> 00:21:07,683
<i>I'm sure he's under tight security.</i>

364
00:21:07,766 --> 00:21:09,017
[WOMAN] <i>You're out late, Boss Emil.</i>

365
00:21:09,101 --> 00:21:11,937
[LUCAS] <i>We need to take back</i>
<i>the millions we worked hard for.</i>

366
00:21:12,020 --> 00:21:13,188
[EMIL] <i>Magnus Roja.</i>

367
00:21:13,272 --> 00:21:15,315
<i>I'm not done settling the score</i>
<i>with him yet.</i>

368
00:21:15,399 --> 00:21:16,233
<i>I'm sorry, bro.</i>

369
00:21:16,316 --> 00:21:19,069
[OLSEN] <i>He raised me like a father.</i>

370
00:21:19,152 --> 00:21:20,487
<i>But I couldn't save him.</i>

371
00:21:22,239 --> 00:21:23,865
<i>What are you doing here?</i>

372
00:21:23,949 --> 00:21:27,244
<i>Because it turns out</i>
<i>it's not just my husband that you stole.</i>

373
00:21:27,327 --> 00:21:28,412
[GRUNTS]

374
00:21:29,955 --> 00:21:31,373
<i>Let's see if Magnus believes you.</i>

375
00:21:31,456 --> 00:21:33,792
<i>I'll tell him you're the one who stole it.</i>

376
00:21:33,875 --> 00:21:36,044
<i>Ayen was never my real rival.</i>

377
00:21:36,128 --> 00:21:38,297
- [MAGNUS]<i> Greta, don't--</i>
<i>- It's time you learned the truth.</i>

378
00:21:38,380 --> 00:21:42,342
<i>The reason your father favors Olsen</i>
<i>more than you is…</i>

379
00:21:42,426 --> 00:21:44,303
<i>You also had an affair with Auntie Wendy?</i>
